This paper focuses on improving self-supervised learning for computer vision tasks, specifically addressing issues such as chromatic aberration and mid-level feature neglect. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of different datasets for testing generalization, which suggests a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG and cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of different network architectures, which could fall under neural networks (cs.NE) or multimedia (cs.MM).
